import React, { Profiler } from 'react'; import './App.css'; import Project from './Components/Project' const flutter = [ "https://www.thesprucepets.com/thmb/LPnj-N-AcGdZRvf7E6y_Hsf2vqo=/4089x2300/smart/filters:no_upscale()/close-up-of-a-hamster-eating-groundnut-635096689-5c525f88c9e77c0001d7c1fa.jpg" ]; const mario = [ "https://github.com/4yerik/images/blob/master/projects/mario-start.jpg?raw=true", "https://github.com/4yerik/images/blob/master/projects/mario_level_one.JPG?raw=true", "https://github.com/4yerik/images/blob/master/projects/mario_level_two.JPG?raw=true", "https://github.com/4yerik/images/blob/master/projects/mario_mushrooms.JPG?raw=true", "https://github.com/4yerik/images/blob/master/projects/mario_castle.JPG?raw=true", "https://github.com/4yerik/images/blob/master/projects/mario_running.JPG?raw=true", ]; const apollo = [ "https://github.com/4yerik/images/blob/master/projects/apollo-login.JPG?raw=true", "https://github.com/4yerik/images/blob/master/projects/apollo-flight-view.JPG?raw=true", "https://github.com/4yerik/images/blob/master/projects/apollo-cart.JPG?raw=true", "https://github.com/4yerik/images/blob/master/projects/apollo-upcoming.JPG?raw=true", ]; const apolloText = "To learn how graphQL and Apollo work together, I followed a tutorial on Apollo's documentation guide." + "In this tutorial, I started with building a schema for my data." + "Afterwards, I connected my server with a REST API." const Projects = () => (
{apolloText}
Github
 ); export default Projects;
